 Employee Salary Calculator Using Static Methods
Create a Java class named SalaryCalculator with static methods to calculate gross salary, deductions, and net salary. Call these methods without creating an object.
Sample Input
Basic Salary = 30000
Allowance = 5000
Deduction = 2000
Sample Output
Gross Salary = 35000
Net Salary = 33000




import java.util.*;
class Main
{
    static int getgross(int basic,int allow)
    {
        return basic+allow;
    }
    static int getnet(int gross,int deduct)
    {
        return gross-deduct;
    }

    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        int basic=30000;
        int allow=5000;
        int deduct=2000;
        int grosssalary= Main.getgross(basic,allow);
        int netsalary= Main.getnet(grosssalary,deduct);
        System.out.println("Gross salary"+grosssalary);
        System.out.println("Netsalary"+netsalary);
    }
    
}
   
